            It all started with understanding structure.
          </blockquote>
          <P class="muted">
            This project was my first real confrontation with the web as a system, not a canvas. Using pure HTML, I focused on semantic layout, accessibility, and clarity — learning how information should be ordered, not just displayed. There were no shortcuts here, only fundamentals. Every tag had a purpose. This project taught me that before anything can scale, it must first make sense.
